22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who's%20The%20Real%20Monster%3F%20A%20Study%20Reveals%20Marsupials'%20Biggest%20Fear%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20found%20that%20wildlife%20around%20the%20world%20fears%20humans%2C%20the%20'super%20predator'%2C%20more%20than%20other%20well-known%20predators%20like%20lions%2C%20leopards%2C%20bears%2C%20and%20wolves.%20The%20most%20recent%20research%20in%20Australia%2C%20conducted%20by%20Western%20University%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Tasmania%2C%20reveals%20that%20marsupials%20in%20the%20country%20are%20more%20afraid%20of%20humans%20than%20they%20are%20of%20foxes%20and%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20research%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3BFear%20of%20the%20Human%20'Superpredator'%20in%20Native%20Marsupials%20and%20Introduced%20Deer%20in%20Australia%2C%26quot%3B%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froyalsocietypublishing.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1098%2Frspb.2023.2849%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejournal%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20Royal%20Society%20B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Australian%20marsupials%20are%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20threats%20humans%20pose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20investigated%20the%20fear%20response%20of%20four%20native%20marsupial%20species%20(eastern%20grey%20kangaroo%2C%20Bennett's%20wallaby%2C%20Tasmanian%20pademelon%2C%20common%20brushtail%20possum)%20and%20a%20non-native%20mammal%20(fallow%20deer)%20by%20exposing%20them%20to%20recordings%20of%20predator%20vocalisations%20(human%2C%20dog%2C%20Tasmanian%20devil%2C%20wolf)%20and%20non-threatening%20sounds%20(sheep).%20The%20results%20were%20clear%3A%20the%20marsupials%20were%20most%20afraid%20of%20humans%2C%20fleeing%202.4%20times%20more%20often%20than%20when%20exposed%20to%20any%20other%20predator.%20They%20were%20also%20significantly%20more%20vigilant%20in%20responding%20to%20human%20sounds.%20This%20research%20adds%20to%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20wildlife%20around%20the%20world%20views%20humans%20as%20the%20top%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20results%20greatly%20expand%20the%20growing%20experimental%20evidence%20that%20wildlife%20worldwide%20perceives%20humans%20as%20the%20planet's%20most%20frightening%20predator%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zanette%2C%20a%20renowned%20wildlife%20ecologist.%20%26quot%3BThe%20very%20substantial%20fear%20of%20humans%20demonstrated%20here%20and%20in%20comparable%20recent%20experiments%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20have%20dramatic%20ecological%20consequences%20because%20other%20new%20research%20has%20established%20that%20fear%20itself%20can%20reduce%20wildlife%20numbers%20and%20that%20fear%20of%20humans%20can%20cause%20cascading%20impacts%20on%20multiple%20species%20throughout%20entire%20landscapes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2024%2F05%2F240522130457.htm%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20conduct%20their%20experiment%2C%20the%20team%20deployed%20hidden%20automated%20camera-speaker%20systems%20that%2C%20when%20triggered%20by%20an%20animal%20passing%20within%20a%20short%20distance%20(approximately%2010%20metres%2C%20or%2030%20feet)%2C%20filmed%20the%20response%20to%20humans%20speaking%20calmly%2C%20dogs%20barking%2C%20Tasmanian%20devils%20snarling%2C%20wolves%20howling%2C%20or%20non-threatening%20controls%2C%20such%20as%20sheep%20bleating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGlobal%20surveys%20show%20humans%20kill%20prey%20at%20much%20higher%20rates%20than%20other%20predators%2C%20making%20humans%20a'super%20predator%2C'%20and%20the%20profound%20fear%20of%20humans%20being%20revealed%20in%20wildlife%20everywhere%20is%20wholly%20consistent%20with%20humanity's%20unique%20lethality%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zanette.%20%26quot%3BHumans%20are%20'the%20invisible%20killer'%20insofar%20as%20we%20do%20not%20often%20think%20of%20ourselves%20as%20a%20major%20predator%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20most%20dangerous%2C%20but%20wildlife%20clearly%20think%20differently%20and%20recognise%20us%20for%20what%20we%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716888420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fv2v952i8_wildlife_625x300_28_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhos-the-real-monster-a-study-reveals-marsupials-biggest-fear-5763210%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Studies%20show%20that%20wildlife%20fears%20'super%20predator'%20more%20than%20other%20predators%2C%20with%20Australian%20marsupials%20demonstrating%20heightened%20fear%20and%20vigilance%20in%20response%20to%20human%20sounds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhos-the-real-monster-a-study-reveals-marsupials-biggest-fear-5763210%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhos-the-real-monster-a-study-reveals-marsupials-biggest-fear-5763210%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhos-the-real-monster-a-study-reveals-marsupials-biggest-fear-5763210%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20solution%20to%20the%20urban%20doom%20loop%20is%20right%20beneath%20our%20feet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skyscraper%20surrounded%20by%20pipe%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a441fec0c69656901bc60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESame%20Green%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETucked%20beneath%20a%2048-story%20San%20Francisco%20skyscraper%2C%20at%20the%20far%20end%20of%20the%20parking%20lot%20on%20the%20first%20subbasement%20level%2C%20is%20a%20door%20with%20a%20keypad%20lock.%20An%20unimposing%20sign%20reads%20%26quot%3BUtility%20Meter%20Room.%26quot%3B%20Behind%20the%20door%20is%20a%20tangled%20clot%20of%20pipes%3A%20yellow%2C%20blue%2C%20and%20orange%2C%20each%20one%20as%20wide%20as%20a%20100-pound%20barbell%20plate.%20The%20pipes%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20thousands%20more%20just%20like%20them%2C%20winding%20their%20way%20under%20more%20than%20600%20American%20cities%2C%20campuses%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20airports%20%E2%80%94%20are%20more%20than%20a%20blast%20from%20our%20industrial%20past.%20They're%20a%20steampunk%20vision%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20come%20to%20345%20California%20Center%2C%20a%20postmodern%20hexagon%20that%20towers%20over%20San%20Francisco's%20financial%20district%2C%20to%20get%20a%20look%20at%20the%20hottest%20new%20idea%20for%20how%20to%20break%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-doom-loop-fix-american-city-housing-transit-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eurban%20doom%20loop%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20post-pandemic%2C%20remote-work%20apocalypse%20that%20is%20hollowing%20out%20America's%20cities.%20And%20when%20I%20say%20%26quot%3Bhottest%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20don't%20mean%20it%20metaphorically.%20It's%20like%20a%20%3Cem%3Esauna%20%3C%2Fem%3Edown%20here.%20Because%20the%20Utility%20Meter%20Room%20doesn't%20run%20on%20a%20self-contained%2C%20industrial-sized%20boiler%2C%20like%20most%20big%20buildings.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20drawing%20a%20feed%20of%20blistering%2C%20high-pressure%2C%20vaporized%20water%20from%20a%20century-old%20loop%20of%20steam%20pipes%20that%20runs%20beneath%20the%20city's%20streets.%20The%20steam%20loops%20are%20a%20relic%20of%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20as%20forgotten%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cabinetmagazine.org%2Fissues%2F41%2Fsteenson.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epneumatic%20tubes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20used%20to%20shoot%20mail%20all%20over%20American%20cities.%20But%20unlike%20the%20pneumatic%20tubes%2C%20the%20steam%20loops%20are%20still%20there%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20can%20provide%20enough%20heat%20to%20keep%20a%20building%20like%20345%20California%20Center%20nice%20and%20toasty%2C%20even%20on%20the%20coldest%20of%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20steam%20loops%20are%20part%20of%20an%20antiquated%20system%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecycling-waste-heat-abundant-sustainable-energy-source-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edistrict%20energy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20basically%20a%20shared-services%20model%3A%20a%20utility%20would%20make%20steam%20at%20a%20central%20location%20and%20then%20pipe%20it%20out%20to%20every%20building%20in%20the%20city.%20Nobody%20had%20to%20provide%20their%20own%20heat%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20way%20more%20convenient%2C%20and%20cheaper%2C%20to%20get%20it%20from%20a%20common%20source.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20cities%20began%20to%20abandon%20district%20energy.%20Buildings%2C%20businesses%2C%20and%20homes%20started%20making%20their%20own%20hot%20water%20in%20boilers%20fueled%20by%20coal%2C%20then%20oil%2C%20then%20natural%20gas.%20Sometimes%20it%20was%20cheaper%2C%20and%20maybe%20it%20was%20more%20convenient.%20But%20it%20also%20set%20the%20planet%20on%20fire.%20More%20heating%20meant%20more%20greenhouse%20gases%2C%20and%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-global-warming-extreme-heat-inflation-global-economy-impact-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eglobal%20warming%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20brings%20me%20back%20to%20our%20steampunk%20future.%20Today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-brag-green-but-offices-have-long-way-to-go-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecities%20are%20starting%20to%20price%20the%20looming%20climate%20catastrophe%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20their%20energy%20costs.%20Starting%20this%20year%2C%20commercial%20buildings%20in%20New%20York%20City%20will%20be%20slapped%20with%20steep%20fines%20if%20they're%20emitting%20too%20much%20carbon.%20Boston%20and%20Washington%20have%20similar%20%26quot%3Bdecarbonization%26quot%3B%20laws%20in%20place%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kqed.org%2Fscience%2F1992085%2Fsan-francisco-will-continue-enforcing-gas-ban-in-new-buildings-despite-berkeleys-repeal-of-similar-rules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESan%20Francisco%20isn't%20allowing%20natural%20gas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20any%20new%20construction.%20That%20means%20businesses%20need%20to%20find%20a%20cleaner%2C%20cheaper%20source%20of%20heat.%20And%20those%20ancient%20steam%20loops%20beneath%20the%20streets%20are%20starting%20to%20seem%20like%20a%20ready-made%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20benefit%20of%20a%20district-energy%20system%2C%20especially%20in%20cities%2C%20is%20the%20distribution%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kevin%20Hagerty%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Vicinity%20Energy.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20city%20wants%20to%20decarbonize%2C%20and%20they%20have%20a%20district-energy%20system%2C%20it's%20much%20easier.%20They%20don't%20have%20to%20change%20things%20on%20a%20building-by-building%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223927%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20orange%20upright%20pipe%20vents%20steam%20into%20the%20night%20sky%20in%20front%20of%20a%20building%20with%20stone%20arches%20and%20gaslamp-type%20lights%2C%20and%20parked%20cars%20on%20an%20urban%20street%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d3463b4abc992e8c7c7c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222946%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELike%20dozens%20of%20cities%2C%20New%20York%20has%20a%20loop%20of%20steam%20pipes%20under%20its%20streets%20that%20could%20help%20reverse%20the%20urban%20doom%20loop.%3Cp%3ELindsey%20Nicholson%2FUCG%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Vicinity%20is%20installing%20what%20will%20be%20the%20nation's%20first%20zero-carbon%20urban%20steam%20loop.%20Drawing%20electricity%20from%20the%20increasingly%20decarbonized%20New%20England%20grid%2C%20powered%20by%20solar%20and%20offshore%20wind%2C%20the%20utility%20will%20use%20the%20energy%20to%20boil%20water%20and%20then%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edeliver%20steam%20directly%20to%20Boston%20office%20buildings%20and%20restaurants%20and%20storefronts%20through%20the%20city's%20antiquated%20maze%20of%20pipes.%20It's%20a%20remnant%20of%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20being%20used%20to%20forestall%20a%20lethal%20climate%20evolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDistrict%20energy%20could%20also%20be%20a%20godsend%20to%20businesses%20struggling%20to%20survive%20the%20current%20landscape%20of%20empty%20offices%20and%20boarded-up%20shops.%20By%20taking%20steam%20right%20out%20of%20the%20street%20beneath%20them%2C%20commercial%20landlords%20can%20pay%20less%20for%20their%20utilities%20and%20avoid%20carbon%20fines%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20they%20can%20lower%20their%20rents%20and%20hold%20on%20to%20tenants%20who%20might%20otherwise%20bail.%20District-energy%20loops%20also%20eliminate%20the%20need%20for%20boilers%20and%20other%20cumbersome%20building%20infrastructure%2C%20freeing%20up%20space%20for%20tenant-grabbing%20amenities%20like%20gyms%2C%20roof-decks%2C%20and%20golf%20simulators.%20(Yep.%20That's%20a%20real%20thing.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20choice%3F%20Spend%20thousands%20to%20upgrade%20a%20building's%20energy%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20cash%20that%20landlords%20don't%20have%20on%20hand%2C%20and%20an%20expense%20they%20can't%20pass%20along%20to%20tenants.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20building%20owner%2C%20district%20energy%20allows%20you%20to%20pay%20a%20small%20premium%20on%20your%20service%20to%20get%20that%20type%20of%20steam%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Blake%20Ellis%2C%20a%20principal%20at%20the%20engineering%20firm%20Burns%20%26amp%3B%20McDonnell.%20%26quot%3BThen%20you%20don't%20have%20that%20big%20capital%20outlay%20you%20probably%20don't%20want%20right%20now%3Cstrong%3E.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEspecially%20if%2C%20as%20in%20many%20downtowns%2C%20your%20building%20is%20only%2070%25%20occupied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20third%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20running%20a%20commercial%20building%20is%20energy.%20And%20according%20to%20one%20major%20study%2C%20a%20building%20as%20energy-efficient%20as%20345%20California%20Center%20can%20charge%2020%25%20more%20for%20rent%20than%20a%20comparable%2C%20inefficient%20building.%20Every%20dollar%20saved%20in%20energy%20costs%2C%20the%20study%20found%2C%20equates%20to%203.5%25%20higher%20rent.%20And%20it's%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20be%20energy%20efficient%20if%20all%20you%20have%20to%20do%20is%20plug%20into%20a%20carbon-free%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esteam%20loop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20building%20is%2040%20years%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20Danz%2C%20the%20chief%20engineer%20for%20345%20Cal%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we're%20using%20the%20latest%20technology%20to%20manage%20our%20energy.%26quot%3B%20He%20points%20to%20the%20gnarl%20of%20pipes%20that%20shoots%20the%20steam%20up%20to%20the%2036th%20floor%2C%20where%20it's%20used%20to%20cook%20a%20water%20supply%20large%20enough%20to%20heat%20the%20entire%20building.%20Having%20a%20boiler%2C%20Danz%20explains%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20another%20system%20we%20would%20have%20to%20provide%20care%20and%20feeding%20for.%26quot%3B%20District%20energy%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20is%20just%20there%20for%20the%20taking%2C%20right%20beneath%20our%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20convincing%20evidence%20that%20steam%20loops%20make%20economic%20sense%20comes%20from%20who's%20getting%20into%20the%20district-energy%20game.%20Vicinity%2C%20the%20nation's%20biggest%20clean-steam%20provider%2C%20is%20owned%20by%20Antin%20Infrastructure%20Partners%2C%20a%20leading%20private-equity%20firm.%20Cordia%2C%20an%20energy%20provider%20operating%20in%2010%20cities%2C%20is%20partially%20owned%20by%20the%20private-equity%20giant%20KKR.%20Everyone%20needs%20heat%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20it%20a%20highly%20bankable%20investment.%20%26quot%3BThese%20private-equity%20funds%20come%20in%20and%20find%20areas%20where%20they%20can%20put%20capital%20into%20a%20business%20and%20get%20a%20nice%20steady%20rate%20of%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20Hagerty%20says.%20%26quot%3BDecarbonizing%20takes%20capital%2C%20and%20private%20equity%20is%20a%20great%20source%20of%20capital.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20of%20course%2C%20private%20equity%20may%20decide%20to%20do%20what%20it%20always%20does%20and%20load%20up%20these%20new%20energy%20businesses%20with%20massive%20amounts%20of%20debt%20before%20dismantling%20them%20for%20parts.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20the%20big%20money%20sees%20big%20profits%20to%20be%20made%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-build-infrastructure-transportation-housing-regulation-environment-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmerica's%20forgotten%20infrastructure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Outside%20of%20places%20like%20airports%20and%20college%20campuses%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20district%20energy%20fell%20out%20of%20favor%20long%20ago.%20We%20let%20the%20systems%20go%20fallow%20%E2%80%94%20but%20fortunately%2C%20all%20the%20accumulated%20infrastructure%20we%20buried%20on%20top%20of%20the%20old%20steam%20loops%20made%20it%20impossible%20to%20dig%20their%20little-used%20pipes%20out%20of%20the%20ground.%20So%20the%20whole%20thing%20was%20still%20down%20there%2C%20waiting%2C%20when%20COVID%20drove%20millions%20of%20city%20dwellers%20to%20head%20for%20the%20countryside.%20Now%2C%20by%20drawing%20heat%20from%20their%20old%20steam%20loops%2C%20America's%20cities%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20jump-start%20all%20the%20downtown%20commerce%20that%20was%20crippled%20by%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20could%20happen%20all%20over%20the%20place!%20Dozens%20and%20dozens%20of%20cities%20have%20steam%20loops%20they%20can%20use%2C%20from%20New%20York%20and%20Chicago%20to%20Miami%20to%20San%20Diego%20and%20Portland%20and%20Milwaukee.%20What's%20more%2C%20lots%20of%20companies%20these%20days%20are%20looking%20for%20greener%20buildings%2C%20both%20to%20save%20money%20and%20to%20burnish%20their%20environmental%20bona%20fides.%20From%20AI%20startups%20to%20biotech%20companies%2C%20steampunk-heated%20buildings%20could%20become%20the%20cool%20new%20place%20to%20be.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForward-minded%20companies%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20building%20that%20doesn't%20have%20any%20on-site%20fossil-fuel%20combustion%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Costa%20Samaras%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Scott%20Institute%20for%20Energy%20and%20Innovation%20at%20Carnegie%20Mellon.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%2C%20greenest%20buildings%20will%20be%20net-zero%20buildings.%20They'll%20be%20considered%20a%20premium%20asset.%20The%20challenge%20is%2C%20are%20we%20going%20to%20get%20enough%20premium%20assets%20in%20time%3F%26quot%3B%20Meaning%3A%20Can%20we%20use%20steam%20loops%20to%20fix%20the%20urban%20doom%20loop%20before%20the%20climate%20doom%20loop%20dooms%20us%20all%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freverse-america-urban-doom-loop-downtown-decline-abandoned-steam-pipes-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716888361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a444410dfcda409677843%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freverse-america-urban-doom-loop-downtown-decline-abandoned-steam-pipes