m%2Freleases%2F2024%2F05%2F240523153645.htm%5C%22%3EA%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Personnel%20Psychology%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20employees%20who%20frequently%20boast%20about%20their%20stress%20levels%20are%20perceived%20as%20less%20competent%20and%20less%20likeable%20by%20their%20colleagues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%2C%20led%20by%20Jessica%20Rodell%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%2C%20aimed%20to%20explore%20the%20effects%20of%20stress-bragging%20in%20the%20workplace.%20Rodell%20and%20her%20team%20conducted%20an%20experiment%20with%20360%20participants%2C%20who%20were%20asked%20to%20evaluate%20statements%20from%20imaginary%20colleagues%20returning%20from%20a%20conference.%20While%20some%20colleagues%20expressed%20enjoyment%2C%20others%2C%20the%20so-called%20busy%20braggers%2C%20lamented%20how%20the%20conference%20added%20to%20their%20already%20overwhelming%20workload.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20behaviour%20we've%20all%20seen%2C%20and%20we%20all%20might%20be%20guilty%20of%20at%20some%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rodell.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20wondering%20about%20why%20people%20do%20this%2C%20I%20thought%20maybe%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20our%20stress%20because%20we%20want%20to%20prove%20we're%20good%20enough.%20We%20found%20out%20that%20often%20backfires.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20harming%20themselves%20by%20doing%20this%20thing%20they%20think%20is%20going%20to%20make%20them%20look%20better%20to%20their%20colleagues%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20investigation%20by%20Rodell's%20team%20involved%20surveying%20218%20real-life%20workers%20about%20their%20experiences%20with%20busy%20braggers%20in%20their%20workplaces.%20The%20findings%20were%20troubling%3A%20exposure%20to%20colleagues%20who%20frequently%20boasted%20about%20their%20busyness%20led%20to%20increased%20levels%20of%20stress%20and%20burnout%20among%20their%20peers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERodell%20explained%20that%20the%20act%20of%20stress-bragging%20creates%20an%20environment%20where%20being%20overwhelmed%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20positive%20trait%2C%20pressuring%20others%20to%20adopt%20a%20similar%20outlook.%20This%20not%20only%20exacerbates%20stress%20but%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20withdrawal%20and%20disengagement%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20noted%20a%20crucial%20distinction%20between%20genuine%20stress%20and%20performative%20anxiety.%20Employees%20who%20authentically%20experience%20and%20express%20stress%20are%20perceived%20more%20sympathetically%20and%20even%20seen%20as%20more%20competent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20genuinely%20feel%20stressed%2C%20it's%20OK%20to%20find%20the%20right%20confidant%20to%20share%20with%20and%20talk%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodell%20advised.%20%26quot%3BBut%20be%20mindful%20that%20it%20is%20not%20a%20badge%20of%20honour%20to%20be%20bragged%20about%20-%20that%20will%20backfire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716882480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F1oh140no_office-generic_625x300_30_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbusy-bragging-is-a-toxic-work-trait-it-makes-you-look-incompetent-study-5762580%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20workplace%2C%20where%20deadlines%20are%20tight%20and%20expectations%20high%2C%20stress%20is%20inevitable%20Yet%2C%20for%20some%2C%20stress%20is%20just%20a%20byproduct%20of%20their%20professional%20life%20-%20a%20badge%20of%20honour.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbusy-bragging-is-a-toxic-work-trait-it-makes-you-look-incompetent-study-5762580%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbusy-bragging-is-a-toxic-work-trait-it-makes-you-